Only 1 failure out of 137 tests! The DepartmentsController Edit POST test has a wrong assertion. I noted that the EF InMemory might return a ViewResult due to concurrency token issues, but apparently it works fine with InMemory (no concurrency check). The controller returns RedirectToActionResult on success. Let me fix the assertion.

Looking at the DepartmentsController Edit POST code:
```csharp
if (ModelState.IsValid)
{
    db.Entry(department).State = EntityState.Modified;
    db.SaveChanges();
    SendEntityNotification(...);
    return RedirectToAction("Index");
}
```

With InMemory provider, SaveChanges succeeds without throwing a concurrency exception, so the method returns RedirectToActionResult as expected. I need to update the test assertion to match this behavior.

